# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Razorpay Payment Gateway Credentials
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get these from https://dashboard.razorpay.com → Settings → API Keys
# Use TEST keys (rzp_test_...) while developing, LIVE keys (rzp_live_...) in production.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development and fill in real values.
# On Vercel, add these as Environment Variables (Project Settings → Environment Variables).
#
# IMPORTANT: RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET must NEVER be exposed to the browser.
# Both variables are read only in server-side API routes.

RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=your_key_id_here
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=your_key_secret_here

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Meta (Facebook) Pixel
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. The Pixel ID is exposed to the browser (that's expected for a
# tracking pixel), so it uses the NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix. If left unset, the app
# falls back to the hard-coded production Pixel ID in src/lib/fbpixel.ts.
# Set this in Vercel → Project Settings → Environment Variables to point a
# preview/staging deployment at a different pixel.
NEXT_PUBLIC_META_PIXEL_ID=7732359703489696


